During the seminars the research projects of the doctoral students will be discussed. In order to present one's project, each participant should hold a presentation on their research results up to the time being, concentrating on the more important aspects. Together with the presentation the student presents also the current structure of the research work. In seminars, doctoral students will acquire skills of presentation, opposition, moderation and discussion. On the basis of presentation also a written paper should be presented.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop the skills of presentation, opposition, moderation and discussion; further development of the research project.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Doctoral student is able to:
study independently research problems;  analyze critically and constructively and oppose the research work; participate argumentatively in discussion.
